# AFK fleet supervisor — one cron entry, every 3
# minutes, ordered passes under one lock.
#
# Activation is manual/opt-in (never auto-enabled). With a cron daemon present,
# install for the current user with (adjust the paths to your environment):
#
#   { crontab -l 2>/dev/null; \
#     echo '*/3 * * * * FLEET_HOME=/path/to/target-repo /path/to/venv/bin/flotilla tick'; \
#   } | crontab -
#
# `flotilla tick` runs one supervisor tick and logs to
# $FLEET_HOME/.claude/fleet/supervisor.log. FLEET_HOME must point at the repo
# the fleet operates on; use the `flotilla` console script from the virtualenv
# flotilla is installed in (it sets FLEET_PYTHON for you).
#
# Many dev images ship NO cron daemon (and no systemd), so the supported
# autostart path there is the opt-in FLEET_AUTOSTART tmux ticker
# (fleet-autostart.sh) / `flotilla start`. This file is for environments that
# DO have cron.
*/3 * * * * FLEET_HOME=/path/to/target-repo /path/to/venv/bin/flotilla tick
